{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "31", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "05", "S": "44"}}, "news": [{"title": "Chennai's town planning department to issue building permits within 27 days", "para": "Chennai's town planning department will now issue building permits within 27 days, aiming to curb corruption and delays. Officials are barred from summoning applicants, with all processes, including payments and clarifications, moving online. This move ensures time-bound, transparent service delivery for the public, streamlining approvals for various building types.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/chennai-government-streamlines-building-permit-process-to-just-27-days/131420508?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-46628/131420508.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "May 31 last date to pay property tax, avail rebate: Chandigarh civic body", "para": "Property owners in Chandigarh have a final chance to save money on their taxes. The municipal corporation is urging everyone to pay by May 31 to secure a 20% rebate on residential and 10% on commercial property tax. Failure to meet this deadline will result in a hefty 25% penalty plus 12% interest.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/final-call-for-property-owners-may-31-deadline-for-tax-payment-to-secure-rebate-in-chandigarh/131420492?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-95998/131420492.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Mumbai property registrations rise 7% to 12,315 units in May 2026: Knight Frank", "para": "Mumbai recorded 12,315 property registrations in May 2026, up seven per cent year-on-year, marking the highest registrations for the month of May in 14 years, according to Knight Frank India. Stamp duty collections stood at \u20b91,051 crore during the month, marginally lower than the year-ago period.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/mumbai-property-registrations-reach-14-year-high-in-may-2026/131420277?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-31564/131420277.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}